fullplot: After the WWI Armistice Lloyd Hart goes back to practice law, former saloon keeper George Hally turns to bootlegging, and out-of-work Eddie Bartlett becomes a cab driver. Eddie builds a fleet of cabs through delivery of bootleg liquor and hires Lloyd as his lawyer. George becomes Eddie's partner and the rackets flourish until love and rivalry interfere.
plot: Three men attempt to make a living in Prohibitionist America after returning home from fighting together in World War I.
title: The Roaring Twenties
writers: Mark Hellinger (from an original story by)
